--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
version 2.2.6.0  |  2013-02-06  |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHG Support of Linux versions from 3.x onwards. [VOICECPE_SW-594]
NEW Added support for XWAY(TM) xRX300 family. [VOICECPE_SW-370]
    Added the XRX300 firmware version identifier.
    Updated the pin reservation for the SSI bus.
CHG Integrated patches from FALCON project. [VOICECPE_SW-379]
FIX Added error check to prevent overwriting memory in case of corrupted data
    in the mailbox.
FIX Cleanup automake from warnings reported by "autoreconf -Wall"
    JIRA_RND [VOICECPE_SW-328]
NEW Configurable FW test feature: --enable-test-cmd-notry [VOICECPE_SW-189]:
    on command write if there is no space in the command downstream mailbox the
    FIO_MPS_MB_WRITE ioctl returns immediately with error code -EIO without
    additional write tries. Mailbox content console trace is suppressed.
    Implemented upon FW team request. Disabled per default.
CHG for xRX platforms: reservation of all GPIO lines used by SmartSLIC (GPIO31,
    GPIO8, GPIO34, GPIO35, GPIO36). Previously only SSLIC RESET (GPIO31) was
    reserved. [VOICECPE_SW-187]
CHG Character device registration/unregistration in the style of linux 2.6.x;
    Dynamic major number allocation.
CHG Patches from Falcon project: FALCON system support and linux-2.6.39
    adaptation
CHG Updated configure arguments.

